{
  "text": "Infections of the tonsillar fossa (peritonsillar abscesses, recurrent and chronic tonsillitis) are considered to be indications for tonsillectomy. Although this is a common surgical procedure, tonsillectomy can be complicated by a major postoperative complication, such as post tonsillectomy bleeding (PTB). The incidence of PTB in adults has been recently reported to be between 2-15%. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [12] Therefore, understanding the factors that may cause PTB is of great interest. PTB was previously associated with the following risk factors: an older age, that is, above 35 years, hot dissection vis-\u00e0-vis cold dissection techniques, complete tonsillectomy in comparison to tonsillotomy, occurrence of a minor post-operative bleeding episode, surgery performed during the winter months, male sex, and blood group O.",
